{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|能|火|c1=p|c2=s|t2=fire|ls=psc}}.

This character originally represented an onomatopoetic word (see [[熊熊]]). Later its phonetic compound [[能]], the character for the Old Chinese word "bear", was borrowed for another word. This character thus began to represent the word "bear" instead.

{{ja-noun|くま|クマ}}

# a [[bear]] {{gl|large mammal of family Ursidae}}
# {{lb|ja|slang|sort=くま}} a [[bear]], an [[otter]] {{gl|a [[hairy]] [[man]], especially one who is [[gay]]}}

{{der-top}}
* {{ja-r|熊%鼠|くま%ねずみ}}: ''{{l|mul|Rattus rattus}}'', the [[black rat]]
* {{ja-r|穴%熊|あな%ぐま}}: ''{{l|mul|Meles meles}}'', the [[Eurasian badger]]
{{der-bottom}}
